  "title": "Product Quality Control Engineer",
  "description": "<h2>WHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE</h2><p>• Products consistently pass inspection and functional/RF testing prior to shipment<br />• Defects are identified early and trend downward over time<br />• Manufacturing trusts inspection and test results<br />• Quality execution scales with production growth</p><h2>WHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR</h2><p>• Hands-on experience executing inspections and functional testing in hardware-focused environments (electronics, RF, aerospace, robotics, or adjacent industries)<br />• Comfort working from drawings, specifications, and test criteria<br />• Hands-on experience with functional and/or RF test execution<br />• Experience documenting nonconformances and supporting corrective actions<br />• Detail-oriented, disciplined, and effective in fast-paced production settings</p>",
